contentrichtext.text: '''Richard Bennet''' or '''Bennett''' may refer to: * [[Richard Bennett (actor)]] (1870–1944), film star and father of actresses Constance Bennett and Joan Bennett * [[Richard Bennett (cricketer)]] (1872–1953), English cricketer * [[Richard Bennett (guitarist)]] (born 1951), Nashville based musician and record producer * [[Richard Bennett (Governor)]] (1609–1675), colonial governor of Virginia * [[Dick Bennett]] (born 1943), basketball coach * Dick Bennett, a character in the film ''[[8 Heads in a Duffel Bag]]'' * [[Richard A. Bennett]] (born 1963), politician from Maine, former president of the Maine Senate * [[R. B. Bennett]] (1870–1947), former prime minister of Canada * [[Richard D. Bennett]] (born 1947), U.S. federal judge * [[Richard E. Bennett]] (born 1946), religion professor at Brigham Young University * [[Richard Rodney Bennett]] (1936–2012), British composer * [[Rick Bennett]] (born 1967), retired American ice hockey left winger. * [[Richard Bennet (MP)]], Member of Parliament (MP) for [[Wycombe (UK Parliament constituency)|Wycombe]] ==See also== * [[Richard Bennett Lamas]] (born 1968), Uruguayan former comic book artist * [[Bennett (disambiguation)]] {{hndis|Bennett, Richard}} {{DEFAULTSORT:Bennett, Richard}}
